   <p>Channa Masala is my favourite dish to eat with chapati or rice</p>
   <p>The list of ingredients to make chane masala are as follows</p>
   <p>I will leave the making of rice / chapati to you</p>
      
   <ol> 
     
     <li>2 cups of chana </li>
     <li>2 tomatoes </li>             
     <li>2 onions </li>     
     <li>2 cloves of garlic </li>     
     <li>A piece of ginger  </li>     
     <li>channa masala poweder </li>
     <li>fourth </li>
     
     </ol>
      <p> Here is the method</p>
      <!-- unordered lists -->
      <ul> 
          <li>Soak the chickpeas (channa) overnight (roughly 8 hours) and then boil till they are soft </li>
        <li>Set boiled channa aside </li>
          <li>fry onion, ginger and garlic in a tbl. spoon of oil </li>
          <li>Add diced tomatoes and bring  it to a  boil </li>
          <li>Add channa masala poweder (store purchased)</li>
        <li>Add boiled chickpeas to the pan</li>
        <li>Boil for antoher 5-8 min till everything combines</li>
        <li>Add salt to taste</li>    
     </ul>
